user_template:
Analyse these rows from the END of a transaction file.

File schema:
- Date column: {date_col}
- Description column: {description_col}
- Amount columns: {amount_info}

Last rows (index 0 = oldest of the tail, higher index = closer to end of file):
{rows_json}

Identify which rows are footer (NOT real transactions).
Return a JSON object with a "footer_rows" array. Each element must have:
- "index": the row index from the input
- "reason": one of "total", "balance", "note", "signature", "empty", "other"

If ALL rows are real transactions, return {"footer_rows": []}.
